//what is schemaa
//schema is a way to define the structure of data in a database. It specifies the fields, their types, and any constraints or relationships between them. In a server context, a schema can be used to validate incoming data, ensuring that it adheres to the expected format before it is processed or stored in the database. This helps maintain data integrity and can prevent errors or security vulnerabilities.

// In the context of a server, a schema can be defined using various libraries or frameworks, such as Mongoose for MongoDB. A schema can include fields like name, email, password, etc., along with their data types (e.g., String, Number) and any validation rules (e.g., required, unique). When a request is made to the server with data that needs to be stored in the database, the server can use the defined schema to validate the data before saving it. This ensures that only valid and properly structured data is stored in the database.

//hinglish me samjhaun to schema ek tarah ka blueprint hota hai jo database me data ke structure ko define karta hai. Isme aap specify karte ho ki kaunse fields honge, unka type kya hoga, aur koi constraints ya relationships honge ya nahi. Server ke context me, schema ka use aap incoming data ko validate karne ke liye kar sakte ho, taaki ensure ho sake ki data expected format me hai ya nahi, isse data integrity maintain hoti hai aur errors ya security vulnerabilities se bachav hota hai.

// Server ke context me, aap schema ko define karne ke liye alag-alag libraries ya frameworks ka use kar sakte ho, jaise ki Mongoose MongoDB ke liye. Schema me aap fields define kar sakte ho jaise name, email, password, etc., unke data types (e.g., String, Number) aur validation rules (e.g., required, unique) ke sath. Jab server ko koi request aati hai jisme data hota hai jo database me store karna hota hai, to server defined schema ka use karke data ko validate kar sakta hai before saving it. Isse ensure hota hai ki sirf valid aur properly structured data hi database me store hota hai.


//what is modal 
// a modal is make easy crud operations on the corresponding collection[simaliar type of data ] in the database. It provides an interface to interact with the database, allowing you to perform operations like creating, reading, updating, and deleting documents in a collection. In a server context, a modal can be used to define the structure of the data and the methods to interact with it, making it easier to manage and manipulate data in the database.

// Modal ek tarah ka interface hota hai jo database ke corresponding collection par CRUD operations ko asaan banata hai. Iska use aap database ke sath interact karne ke liye kar sakte ho, jisme aap create, read, update, aur delete operations perform kar sakte ho collection me documents par. Server ke context me, modal ka use aap data ke structure aur uske sath interact karne ke methods ko define karne ke liye kar sakte ho, jisse database me data ko manage aur manipulate karna asaan ho jata hai.